#  googleVis
```{r,results = "asis"}
options(gvis.plot.tag='chart')
library(googleVis)
df=data.frame(country=c("US", "GB", "BR"), 
              val1=c(10,13,14), 
              val2=c(23,12,32))
Line <- gvisLineChart(df)
.z.show.googleVis(Line)
Motion=gvisMotionChart(Fruits, 
                       idvar="Fruit", 
                       timevar="Year")
.z.show.googleVis(Motion)

Geo <- gvisGeoChart(Exports, locationvar='Country', colorvar='Profit',
options=list(height=300, width=350))
Tbl <- gvisTable(Exports, options=list(height=300, width=200))
.z.show.googleVis(gvisMerge(Geo, Tbl, horizontal=TRUE))
print(Line, tag='chart')
```

# rCharts
```{r results = 'asis', comment = NA}
require(rCharts)
data(economics, package = 'ggplot2')
econ <- transform(economics, date = as.character(date))
m1 <- mPlot(x = 'date', y = c('psavert', 'uempmed'), type = 'Line',
  data = econ)
m1$set(pointSize = 0, lineWidth = 1)
.z.show.rCharts(m1)
```
